Reasoning: The paper deals with the multiplexing gain region of cellular networks, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also considers delay constraints, which are a key aspect of networked systems, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely sub-category. The use of cooperative communication and the analysis of the performance of cellular networks suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves some mathematical modeling and analysis, which could make cs.MM (Mathematical Modeling) a relevant sub-category as well.
